Law: For what reason have you come?

Hestia: ...but everyone is still very grateful!

Hestia: Y-Y-Y-You! What are you doing here again! Being beaten was not enough!?

Law: ...Oh...

Joan: Ahhhhhh, old sir, please let us pass!

Joan: Oh, sorry Master. I'm unable to change my bad habits...
Law: Ergh, erghhh, these little brats are an absolute mess!
Law: In former days, when I saw an elder I showed my respects. Are the lads and lasses in current times all this rude and impetuous?
Law: Young ones...?
Law: To serve as a model for others is a much harder task than to struggle for leadership in some Alliance.
Law: Yet, to be hung up on this is to linger on the aftertaste of sweet wine from days past. Ye dost share my thoughts, don't ye, old friend?
